From: Dave Stevenson <dave.stevenson@raspberrypi.org>
Date: Fri, 7 Jun 2019 11:35:01 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 353/587] defconfigs: Add FB_SIMPLE to both bcmrpi and bcm2709
 configs

The firmware sets up simple fb should one of the KMS drivers
be enabled, but the driver isn't being built.
Add it to the build.

Signed-off-by: Dave Stevenson <dave.stevenson@raspberrypi.org>
---
 arch/arm/configs/bcm2709_defconfig | 1 +
 arch/arm/configs/bcmrpi_defconfig  | 1 +
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/configs/bcm2709_defconfig b/arch/arm/configs/bcm2709_defconfig
index 435052f04bea..ab6e89f0159e 100644
--- a/arch/arm/configs/bcm2709_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/configs/bcm2709_defconfig
@@ -922,6 +922,7 @@ CONFIG_TINYDRM_REPAPER=m
 CONFIG_FB=y
 CONFIG_FB_BCM2708=y
 CONFIG_FB_UDL=m
+CONFIG_FB_SIMPLE=y
 CONFIG_FB_SSD1307=m
 CONFIG_FB_RPISENSE=m
 # CONFIG_BACKLIGHT_GENERIC is not set
diff --git a/arch/arm/configs/bcmrpi_defconfig b/arch/arm/configs/bcmrpi_defconfig
index 26d396170cc2..fe829406de8d 100644
--- a/arch/arm/configs/bcmrpi_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/configs/bcmrpi_defconfig
@@ -914,6 +914,7 @@ CONFIG_TINYDRM_REPAPER=m
 CONFIG_FB=y
 CONFIG_FB_BCM2708=y
 CONFIG_FB_UDL=m
+CONFIG_FB_SIMPLE=y
 CONFIG_FB_SSD1307=m
 CONFIG_FB_RPISENSE=m
 # CONFIG_BACKLIGHT_GENERIC is not set
